  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://slack.rook.io/).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nWhen starting a cluster in OpenShift with the VolumeClaimTemplate for mons, the mons fail to start. \r\n\r\nThe mon log shows:\r\n```\r\nunable to stat setuser_match_path /var/lib/ceph/mon/ceph-a/store.db: (2) No such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe pod description shows a couple errors:\r\n```\r\n      Reason:  PostStartHookError: rpc error: code = Unknown desc = command error: nsenter: failed to open /proc/103597/ns/ipc: No such file or directory\r\nexec failed: container_linux.go:336: starting container process caused \"process_linux.go:86: executing setns process caused \\\"exit status 21\\\"\"\r\n, stdout: , stderr: , exit code -1\r\n\r\nWarning  FailedPostStartHook     10m                kubelet, ip-10-0-136-202.ec2.internal  Exec lifecycle hook ([chown --recursive --verbose ceph:ceph /var/log/ceph]) for Container \"mon\" in Pod \"rook-ceph-mon-a-7f4555598d-4fsjh_rook-ceph(7eb9a5d4-b963-11e9-ba66-1292db96ab4e)\" failed - error: rpc error: code = Unknown desc = command error: nsenter: failed to open /proc/99567/ns/ipc: No such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere appears to be an issue with the pod lifecycle hook to run with the ceph user.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nThe mons should start successfully on OpenShift when based on PVs.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n",
